race.description: Kia Ora Bloodlines To Headlines Handicap
race.comment: ZAMBALES (2) Pinatubo colt from the good producer Calliope on debut for the Anthony & Sam Freedman yard. Has impressed in both trials and the stable will be hoping he's as good as his half-sister Tempted. No excuses from the draw. CALOOCAN BEAUTY (5) Justify filly from Sahara Breeze on debut for the Waterhouse & Bott stable. Looks ready to go after finishing runner-up in her two trials. Each-way contender. OH YES SHE DID (4) returns after making her debut with a slashing fourth in the G3 Gimcrack Stakes at this track and trip last October. Fitted with the one trial and look for her launching late down the outside. SEQUINNED (11) is a Pinatubo filly on debut for Chris Waller and is a half to Bivouac. Gets the key booking of McDonald and is sure to be very competitive.
